location in the home.

00:39:58.730 --> 00:40:00.510
You're not tied to
your router, is often

00:40:00.510 --> 00:40:02.657
in the basement or
some obscure place.

00:40:02.657 --> 00:40:04.490
And the reason was we
wanted to get the best

00:40:04.490 --> 00:40:06.690
signal to talk to all the
devices that you have.

00:40:06.690 --> 00:40:08.271
So the key, though
is getting this

00:40:08.271 --> 00:40:09.520
onto your local Wi-Fi network.

00:40:09.520 --> 00:40:12.900
And what we've done is created
a proprietary technology

00:40:12.900 --> 00:40:15.550
that essentially takes
your Wi-Fi credentials

00:40:15.550 --> 00:40:19.580
that you that you have
on your iPhone or iPad

00:40:19.580 --> 00:40:22.130
and then transmits that
optically to the hub.

00:40:22.130 --> 00:40:25.280
So if you just enter
our password, hit done,

00:40:25.280 --> 00:40:28.910
replace the iPad right
onto the hub and optically,

00:40:28.910 --> 00:40:32.560
it's transmitting the data to
the hub, and within 30 seconds,

00:40:32.560 --> 00:40:34.832
we'll get notification
that the hub is now

00:40:34.832 --> 00:40:36.750
on your local WiFi network.

00:40:36.750 --> 00:40:38.890
And as soon as it does,
it'll automatically

00:40:38.890 --> 00:40:40.670
start discovering
these great devices

00:40:40.670 --> 00:40:44.450
like Sonos, Nest, Phillips Hue.

